    "196244589": {
      "title": "Appropriate body-mass index for Asian populations and its implications for policy and intervention strategies",
      "abstract": "to 25 kg/m 2 in different Asian populations; for high risk it varies from 26 kg/m 2 to 31 kg/m 2 . No attempt was made, therefore, to redefine cut-off points for each population separately. The consultation also agreed that the WHO BMI cut-off points should be retained as international classifications. The consultation identified further potential public health action points (23·0, 27·5, 32·5, and 37·5 kg/m 2 ) along the continuum of BMI, and proposed methods by which countries could make decisions about the definitions of increased risk for their population."
